Woolworths Pays Ian Moir $1.7 Million in His First Year as Chief Executive

-- B y   J a n i c e   K e w
-- 
2011-10-11T06:02:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/woolworths-pays-ian-moir-1-7-million-in-his-first-year-as-chief-executive.html
Woolworths Holdings Ltd., a South
African clothing and food retailer, paid Chief Executive Officer
Ian Moir 13.6 million rand ($1.7 million) in his first year at
the helm of the company as sales rose.  Moir earned 5.3 million rand as his total guaranteed pay in
the 12 months through June and 8.3 million rand as a performance
bonus, Cape Town-based Woolworths said in its 2011  annual
report , posted on its website.  Woolworths’ sales rose 9 percent to 25.8 billion in the
year through June 26 as it opened new stores. The retailer’s
shares have gained 46 percent over the past 12 months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Janice Kew in Johannesburg at 
